  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial: coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence spans nominal operating conditions (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM); extreme low-flow/high-speed edge cases and stagnation-zone shear-stress boundary conditions explicitly named in the COU are not covered by linked validation results — edge-case studies are described as conducted separately in companion work.",
